<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div style="background-color: #1e3932; padding: 64px 40px 48px 40px; text-align: center;">
    <div style="max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #cba258; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Civic Literacy</p>
        <h1 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 46px; color: #f2edd7; margin: 0 0 24px 0; line-height: 1.2;">What barriers to voting exist<br />in the US today, and how do we<br />decide which ones to correct<br /><em style="color: #cba258;">or create?</em></h1>
        <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 17px; color: #d4e9e2; line-height: 1.8; max-width: 660px; margin: 0 auto;">This is our essential question. It will guide everything you research, discover, and present over the next seven days. Keep coming back to it.</p>
    </div>
</div>
<div style="background-color: #f2edd7; padding: 64px 40px;">
    <div style="max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #1e3932; margin: 0 0 14px 0;">Before We Begin</p>
        <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 34px; color: #1e3932; margin: 0 0 32px 0;">Here's the story:</h2>
        <div style="background-color: #ffffff; border-left: 5px solid #CBA258; padding: 30px 34px; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.85; margin: 0;">Right now, today, fewer Americans are voting than they could be, especially young people and certain communities. And this is not a new story.</p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.85; margin: 0;">&nbsp;</p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.85; margin: 0;"><img src="https://pitt.instructure.com/courses/186925/files/15456231/preview" alt="image.png" data-api-endpoint="https://pitt.instructure.com/api/v1/courses/186925/files/15456231" data-api-returntype="File" /></p>
        </div>
        <div style="background-color: #ffffff; border-left: 5px solid #CBA258; padding: 30px 34px; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.85; margin: 0;">For hundreds of years, America has been putting barriers in place to keep certain people from voting. Some were <strong>explicit</strong>: you couldn't vote if you were Black, if you were a woman, if you couldn't read, or if you didn't own property. Those barriers were written directly into law.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background-color: #ffffff; border-left: 5px solid #CBA258; padding: 30px 34px; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.85; margin: 0;">But here's the thing: we legally removed many of those barriers. And yet, people still aren't voting. The barriers <strong>changed shape</strong>. They became harder to see, but just as real.</p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.85; margin: 0;"><img src="https://pitt.instructure.com/courses/186925/files/15456232/preview" alt="image.png" data-api-endpoint="https://pitt.instructure.com/api/v1/courses/186925/files/15456232" data-api-returntype="File" /></p>
        </div>
        <div style="background-color: #ffffff; border-left: 5px solid #CBA258; padding: 30px 34px; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.85; margin: 0;">And right now, as we have this conversation, we are <strong>adding new ones</strong>. Polling sites are being removed near university campuses. Mail-in ballot access is being restricted. New federal proposals would require proof of citizenship to register, which creates real hurdles for millions of legal voters. Transportation in rural areas, work schedules, language access: these are not hypothetical problems. They are happening now.</p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.85; margin: 0;"><img src="https://pitt.instructure.com/courses/186925/files/15456238/preview" alt="image.png" width="320" height="142" data-api-endpoint="https://pitt.instructure.com/api/v1/courses/186925/files/15456238" data-api-returntype="File" /><img src="https://pitt.instructure.com/courses/186925/files/15456240/preview" alt="image.png" width="320" height="264" data-api-endpoint="https://pitt.instructure.com/api/v1/courses/186925/files/15456240" data-api-returntype="File" /></p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.85; margin: 0;"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://pitt.instructure.com/courses/186925/files/15456241/preview" alt="image.png" width="400" height="94" data-api-endpoint="https://pitt.instructure.com/api/v1/courses/186925/files/15456241" data-api-returntype="File" /></p>
        </div>
        <div style="background-color: #1e3932; border-left: 5px solid #CBA258; padding: 30px 34px; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;">
            <p style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 20px; color: #f2edd7; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0; font-style: italic;">So the question becomes: why do we keep creating barriers to voting? And when we find them, do we actually want to fix them, or are some of them necessary protections for a fair election? That is what you are going to investigate.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
