<div style="background-color: #ffffff; padding: 64px 40px;">
    <div style="max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 32px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <div style="background-color: #1e3932; border-radius: 50%; width: 62px; height: 62px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0;"><span style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 26px; color: #cba258;">1</span></div>
            <div>
                <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: #cba258; margin: 0 0 4px 0;">Day One</p>
                <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 30px; color: #1e3932; margin: 0;">The Data Tells a Story</h2>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: #333; line-height: 1.85; margin: 0 0 30px 0;">Today we open the conversation. You are going to look at real data on voter participation in the United States, and you are going to start asking your own questions about what you see. By the end of today, you will already have the beginning of a direction for your research.</p>
        <div style="background-color: #f2edd7; border-radius: 10px; padding: 28px 32px; margin-bottom: 24px;">
            <h3 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 20px; color: #1e3932; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">What We're Doing Today</h3>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px;">
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start;">
                    <div style="background-color: #cba258; border-radius: 50%; width: 28px; height: 28px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px;"><span style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #1e3932;">1</span></div>
                    <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;"><strong>Data Exploration:</strong> <a class="inline_disabled" href="https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2025/06/26/voter-turnout-2020-2024/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">We will look at voter turnout data across the US</a>, including demographic breakdowns and <a class="inline_disabled" href="https://www.ncsbe.gov/results-data/voter-turnout/2024-general-election-turnout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">North Carolina-specific numbers</a>. What do you notice? What surprises you?</p>
                </div>
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start;">
                    <div style="background-color: #cba258; border-radius: 50%; width: 28px; height: 28px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px;"><span style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #1e3932;">2</span></div>
                    <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;"><strong>Small Group Discussion:</strong> At your table, talk through what the data is showing. Who is voting? Who isn't? What patterns do you see across demographics, regions, and age groups?</p>
                </div>
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start;">
                    <div style="background-color: #cba258; border-radius: 50%; width: 28px; height: 28px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px;"><span style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #1e3932;">3</span></div>
                    <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;"><strong>Whole Class:</strong> We come back together to name what we're seeing. What barriers are already surfacing from the data? What questions are forming?</p>
                </div>
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start;">
                    <div style="background-color: #cba258; border-radius: 50%; width: 28px; height: 28px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px;"><span style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #1e3932;">4</span></div>
                    <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;"><strong>Introduction to Barriers:</strong> We will look at high-level categories of barriers to voting today, including the voter registration process, and start identifying which demographics and situations are most affected. This includes barriers people want to remove and barriers people want to add.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start;">
                    <div style="background-color: #cba258; border-radius: 50%; width: 28px; height: 28px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px;"><span style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #1e3932;">5</span></div>
                    <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #1a1a1a; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;"><strong>Begin Generating Questions:</strong> Based on what you have seen today, what are you starting to wonder? Start thinking about what direction your research might take.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="background-color: #1e3932; border-radius: 10px; padding: 24px 30px;">
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #cba258; margin: 0 0 8px 0;">A Note on Days 6 and 7</p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #d4e9e2; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0;">I will share today how we are going to present your findings at the end of this lesson. We are reimagining what civic conversation looks like when we step away from screens and actually listen to one another. Think coffee house. Think real discourse. More details coming, but start thinking about it now.</p>
