<div style="background-color: #f2edd7; padding: 64px 40px;">
    <div style="max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 32px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <div style="background-color: #cba258; border-radius: 50%; width: 62px; height: 62px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0;"><span style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 20px; color: #1e3932;">6-7</span></div>
            <div>
                <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: #1e3932; margin: 0 0 4px 0;">Days Six and Seven</p>
                <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 30px; color: #1e3932; margin: 0;">The Coffee House</h2>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="background-color: #1e3932; border-radius: 10px; padding: 32px 36px; margin-bottom: 24px;">
            <p style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 21px; color: #f2edd7; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 18px 0; font-style: italic;">"In 18th century London, people gathered in coffeehouses to talk about ideas that mattered. No screens. No hiding. Just people listening to one another."</p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #d4e9e2; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0;">We're not pretending that civic discourse happens in coffeehouses across America today. But we are going to reimagine what it could look like when we step away from our screens and actually listen to another human being speak in front of us. That is what these two days are about.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background-color: #ffffff; border-radius: 10px; padding: 28px 32px; margin-bottom: 22px;">
            <h3 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 20px; color: #1e3932; margin: 0 0 18px 0;">How It Works</h3>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 15px;">
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start;"><span style="color: #cba258; font-size: 20px; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 1.4;">☕</span>
                    <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #333; margin: 0; line-height: 1.75;">The classroom will be rearranged. Expect a different setup. We are creating a space that feels less like school and more like a real gathering place for ideas.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start;"><span style="color: #cba258; font-size: 20px; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 1.4;">☕</span>
                    <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #333; margin: 0; line-height: 1.75;">Coffee and tea will be available. You're welcome to have some.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start;"><span style="color: #cba258; font-size: 20px; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 1.4;">☕</span>
                    <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #333; margin: 0; line-height: 1.75;">Nothing on your desk except a journal. You are here to listen and take notes on what your peers are sharing. No laptops, no phones.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start;"><span style="color: #cba258; font-size: 20px; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 1.4;">☕</span>
                    <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #333; margin: 0; line-height: 1.75;">When it is your turn to present, you choose: sit in a comfortable chair at the front of the room, or stand at the podium. Your call.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start;"><span style="color: #cba258; font-size: 20px; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 1.4;">☕</span>
                    <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #333; margin: 0; line-height: 1.75;">Presentation order is random. You will find out the day of. Be ready to go from the very start of Day 6, because you might be first.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start;"><span style="color: #cba258; font-size: 20px; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 1.4;">☕</span>
                    <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #333; margin: 0; line-height: 1.75;">If time allows on Day 7, we will hold a Socratic conversation across everything the class has shared. What did we learn? Where do we agree? Where do we genuinely disagree, and why?</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="background-color: #1e3932; border-radius: 10px; padding: 28px 32px;">
            <h3 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 20px; color: #f2edd7; margin: 0 0 14px 0;">Your Artifact</h3>
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #d4e9e2; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 14px 0;">You choose the format. Slides, a poster, a video, something else. What matters is that you have a tangible artifact that represents your research and your argument. Think about what format best tells the story of the barrier you investigated.</p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; color: #d4e9e2; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0;">Whatever you present must be grounded in your research: data, scholarly sources, and an honest engagement with whether this barrier should be corrected, kept, or created. You tell us what you found. We decide what we think.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
